The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bonus buzz irks Spain
                                                                                                                       7                                      Bonus buzz irks Spain
                      
	Murcia: Spain will reportedly receive the most money out of all 32 World Cup teams if they win the World Cup, and several Spanish political parties are unhappy at the figure with the country facing an economic crisis. The Spanish media said each player could earn $734,000 for winning the title, and collect $144,000 just for reaching the July 11 final.         
	10 deported         
	Johannesburg: Ten Argentine hooligans who were said to be planning acts of violence at the World Cup have been deported to Angola after having been detained at South Africas main airport.         
	Good news         
	Tegucigalpa: Honduras midfielder Wilson Palacios will be fit for the World Cup despite a leg muscle injury scare at the weekend, Honduran media reported on Monday.         
	Sudden death         
	Lilongwe: A Dutch soccer fan travelling overland has died en route in Malawi, the police said late on Sunday. Sixty-year-old Henk Witjs, part of a 100-strong group of Dutch fans who wanted to get to the tournament by road, drowned last week in Lake Malawi after ignoring warnings about strong currents.         
	Fifa warning         
	Johannesburg: Fifa president Sepp Blatter said Monday the stadium stampede is like a wake-up call to warn World Cup organisers. I am sure, and you are sure, that this is like an alarm clock and this will not happen at any match at the World Cup, Blatter said.         
